--jboots (camp hoping for a pop and not to be KSed)<br>
--fishbone earring (again camp hoping not to be KSed by your friendly wiz bound there)<br>
--ragefire (oh yeah this is challenging..when i did it i got a new high score on gems..woot loads of fun)<br>
<br>
this is for UT<br>
<br>
i do tons of rvr and this is not first pvp/rvr game i've played and i love it...yes sometimes it's just run forward and best the hell out of whoever you see...but other times you have to think and plan your attack<br>
taking over forts has as much reward as an EQ raid on cazic...lots of killing to get to the big mob..kill him and brag that you did it...yes EQ a couple items drop but in reality you killed caizc to say you did...that why i take over forts..to say i was there and did it (really hope they add some rewards for this though..would make it even more fun)<br>
EXPing past 40...same as EQ slow and tedious..same amount of 40+ zones that EQ had at launch..about same drop rate on rare items so no real difference here other than group of up to 8 for daoc and only 6 for EQ (again i will point out..some of the 40+ zones are not itemized...you get cash only...but 90% of the people are there for exp anyways just like EQ..drops are a plus)<br>
player driven economy....while i agree it could be better..the tradeskills system is 10 times better than EQ has ever been....daoc player made gear is majority of the time better than dropped and easier to get...you can dye gear any color you want (in my opnion this is very nice option) so no more mismatched gear hoping you get all the drops of that type of armor just to match...yes daoc gear wears down sub 40 this is no prob because you outgrow gear before it wears out..past 40 it actually makes you think which item to use in which situation (in my opnion this reflects more real life than EQ since EQ you can use the same gear for many many lvs and never have to worry about it wearing out)<br>
quest system---sub 40 quest systems is great..great story behind quest..difficult but not evercamps like EQ...most quests you are able to solo but maybe not at the lv it's given...if you have 3 people on same quest you only have to do it once and all 3 (if in group at kill) get the quest item (virtually cuts out any reason to KS).....past 40 they need a little work..they just added 40 epics which the reward is nice but the quest itself is a little tidious<br>
overall attitude of players....they player attitude seems to be more adult like in daoc over EQ..many many times in EQ i felt like i was in a AOL chatroom over an online game...people (for the most part) respect everyone else around them<br>
while i do agree with Ut on the main part that daoc shouldn't have been release in the state it was in i disagree that it isn't fun to play (even past 40)...any class can solo (some not as good as others) and finding groups for the most part is fairly easy also (from team of 3 up to <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ....RvR does need some revamping...most importantly relics and some reward system<br>
yes the are putting in bounty points and relics can be taken now (if server doesn't crash from overload in 1 zone like EQ does) i would like to see a noticable reward system to stats for realm points <p>Flyntt Fyreforge
41 Berserker
