<br>
People like to call EQ a carebear game, however I think that is wrong.  EQ is very much PvP, only its not a blood and guts PvP, its an "economic" or "resource" or "social" one.  It's about having better duds and therefore being ranked higher on the "ladder" than your neighbor.  It's about having better toys than your neighbor, trying to making him/her envious of what you have.  It's the only thing that I can think of that explains why people put up with the LONG LONG LONG camps for stuff.  Being an Explorer, and not an Achiever, perhaps I will never understand.<br>
<br>
In DAoC, that "ladder" is measured in RP, since equipment is so ubiquitous.<br>
<br>
What ever happened to playing a game for fun?  Mythic seems to be making SOOO many of the same damn mistakes that Verant made.  DAoC is populated with people who want to be in Doom /god mode.  The thought of 10 level 35s killing a level 50 makes their skin crawl.  Oh heaven forbid.<br>
<br>
Bring back the fun.  Show me the fun.  Let me play the game for fun.<br>
<br>
OBTW, I am more and more convinced that future MMORPGs will need to set up different servers with different rule sets.  There is never going to be ONE set of rules that satisfies everyone.  Why try?  Let the customers decide what rulesets they want to play with. <p>-----------<BR>
